<p>Say I have Form A, B &amp; confirmation.jsp which holds no form.</p>  <p>Form A has the initial parameter:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;input class="likes" name="likes" readonly type="hidden" value="&lt;c:out value="${likes}"/&gt;"/&gt;  </code></pre>  <p>Form B requests the parameter from A:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;input class="likes" name="likes" readonly type="text" value="&lt;%= request.getParameter("likes")%&gt;"/&gt;   </code></pre>  <p>confirmation.jsp requests the parameter from B, to display the info on the page:  </p>  <pre><code> &lt;c:set var="likedProduct" value="&lt;%= request.getParameter("likes")%&gt;"/&gt;  &lt;c:out value="likedProduct"/&gt; </code></pre>  <p>Strangely, Form A &amp; B hold the inputs perfectly fine. I switched it from <code>hidden</code> to <code>text</code> to see if the variables were there in the first place and yest they are.</p>  <p>But confirmation.jsp does not display the variable. It is blank with not even <code>null</code>, just pure nada. How come?             </p>